SERVICE CLOUD
Set Up Voice ID

Stop asking endless security questions to authenticate your customers over the phone. Instead, use Voice ID powered by Amazon Connect. Using a caller’s voice biometrics, Voice ID verifies the identity of the caller and detects fraud risk.

This feature is available with these telephony models:

SERVICE CLOUD VOICE WITH AMAZON CONNECT	SERVICE CLOUD VOICE WITH PARTNER TELEPHONY FROM AMAZON CONNECT	SERVICE CLOUD VOICE WITH PARTNER TELEPHONY

To use Voice ID, you must have the Service Cloud Voice Additional AWS Services add-on license.

Enable Voice ID in Amazon Connect
To use Amazon Connect’s Voice ID feature, you must first enable it.
Enable Agents to Use Voice ID
By default, only Amazon Connect admins can use Voice ID. To grant agents permission to use it, enable Voice ID in the Agent security profile in Amazon Connect.

Add the Voice ID Component to the Agent’s Work Area
To enable agents to enroll customers in Voice ID, add the Voice ID component to the Omni-Channel widget, Voice Call record page, or both–wherever the agents work.

Create an Amazon Connect Contact Flow with Voice ID
To ask callers if they would like to use voice authentication, create a contact flow. Create a contact flow for all call types for which you want to use Voice ID.

Enable Voice ID in Amazon Connect

Log in to Amazon Connect console at https://console.aws.amazon.com/connect/.
Read the BIPA Consent Acknowledgment, and accept if you agree.
In the Domain Setup section, enter the domain.
Under Encryption, create or enter your AWS KMS key for encrypting your Voice ID domain.
Choose Enable Voice ID.

Enable Agents to Use Voice ID

Log in to Amazon Connect console at https://console.aws.amazon.com/connect/.
Go to Users | Security Profiles.
Edit the Agent security profile.
Under the Contact Control Panel (CCP) section, select Voice ID.
Save your changes.

Add the Voice ID Component to the Omni-Channel Widget
To enable agents to enroll customers in Voice ID directly from the Omni-Channel widget, add the Voice ID component in the Omni-Channel widget.

Add the Voice ID Component to the Voice Call Record Page
To enable agents to enroll customers in Voice ID directly from the Voice Call record page, add the Voice ID component to the Voice Call record page.
title: Voice Biometrics for Customer Authentication
